<p><b>What is the meaning of BPR6ES in NGK?</b> So again, in the case of BPR6ES, the '6' indicates it is suitable for mid range heat. After the number, the next letter or letters identify the reach of the spark plug. The reach is distance between the point at which it runs out of thread at the metal shell and the ground electrode at the end of the spark plug.</p>
